  "instructions": [
    "Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Mince the garlic and ginger, then add them to the saucepan and cook for another minute.",
    "Add the jasmine rice to the saucepan and stir to coat with the vegetable mixture.",
    "Add the apple cider vinegar, honey, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper, and stir-fry for 1-2 minutes.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover the saucepan with a tight-fitting lid, and cook for 15-20 minutes, or until the liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender.",
    "Fluff the rice with a fork and garnish with chopped parsley.",
    "Serve the pilaf warm or at room temperature.",
    "Store leftovers in the refrigerator for up to 3 days."
